    "body": "`.exists()` probably should be postponed until there is a consensus on what that means in Ethereum, however when looking at the account cleanup rules during creation/selfdestruct/etc. should be a good indication.\r\n\r\nI actually don't think this can be done properly without support form a new EVM opcode, because one could check for balance and code size, but cannot check for storage, which is possible to be non-empty if the account is only used through delegatecalls.",
